- Reduce of mana usage.<br>
- Reduce of fizzles<br>
<br>
Effects not related to Specialization, as confirmed by Verant:<br>
- Chance to get interrupted (Defense and Dodge skill, AGI possibly)<br>
- Recovering from interruptions (Channeling only)<br>
- Casting times<br>
<br>
There are two specializations that are interesting for a Magician:<br>
<br>
Conjuration - it helps in casting summon spells and the shock series of DD nukes.<br>
Evocation    - it helps in nuking almost (?) all other nukes.<br>
<br>
Up to 43 most of the Magicians nukes are Evocation based, so I went for Evocation. Having 200 int I rarely have to bother about mana management, the pool is big and I feel it was the right decision. Nuking is what I do most, and I need the mana and time advantage _during_ the fights, more than during downtime, where most summoning sessions take place.<br>
<br>
However, as said, I have more mana during fights than I need anyway (at least soloing). At 44 the new DD is a shock spell and according to many posts the pet chain summoning tactic becomes viable (if not recommendable).. This means, I'll need a lot of Conjuration based spells from 44 on, not only during downtime but in fights as well.<br>
<br>
So I wonder, should I undertake the Temple of Ro quest to reset specializations and switch to Conjuration, even if it will probably take weeks to get it to the level where I now have Evocation (close to 200)?<br>
<br>
